kitten won't use litterbox a friend of mine has a kitten that is about months old she has had her since she was about weeks old the kitten will not use a litterbox my friend has tried different brands of litter shut her in one room w the litterbox while she is at work frequently placed her in the box etc w o success her older cat uses one with no problem anybody have any suggestions smart sses need not respond you can try sprinkling a layer of garden potting soil on the top of the litter it smells nice and natural to a kitty hopefully the kitty won't start peeing in the plants as well but they seem to like the smell and texture of soft potting soil place the kitty right in the box and encourage his front paws to feel the soft soil is there any difficulty getting in or out of the litter box you may want to put a separate box for each kitty maybe he thinks the one box is only for the other cat after all of these attempts i'd be tempted to talk to a vet Cat Kitten Guinea pig Garfield Dog Poker jargon Ferret Domestic rabbit Fancy rat Genericized trademark RuneScape quests Ron and Fez Tofu Sulfur Toxoplasmosis Hello Kitty Homer Simpson Shaggy dog story Japanese Bobtail (cat) Soap opera Eucalyptus Nepeta Azumanga Daioh Feral cat Cats (musical) Pet skunk Cat litter Treecat Soil Chocolate Badly Drawn Kitties Mattress Smells Like Teen Spirit Cannabis cultivation Kurt Cobain Garden Strawberry Eric Cartman Toilet humour Kitty Kelley Socialization Phoebe Buffay's songs Big Brother UK series 5 Little Britain Houseplant Friends Phoebe Buffay USS Kitty Hawk (CV-63) Country parks and conservation in Hong Kong Japanese tea ceremony OpenBSD Abstraction Gray Wolf Cheating in poker Cheetah Stratification (botany) Earthworm The Time Machine Bonsai Kitchen Mac OS X Manx (cat) Xiaolin Showdown Cornish Rex The Weakest Link Burial Kakapo Nirvana (band) Snooker Neko the Kitty Textile manufacturing Desert Coffee Red Forman Carnivorous plant Garfield and Friends Spirit rover timeline for 2004 